history.content:
Many sections' waitlists are full.

Depending on your major (e.g. if you're undeclared), you may not qualify for any of the seats in the lecture, which means that whether or not the lecture is open is irrelevant. And if you can't get directly into lecture, you have to waitlist, so whether or not your section has open seats is irrelevant.

I checked and there's still space on the waitlist for the lecture. Steven is right, many sections (and the section waitlists) are full. Try enrolling with a different section. If you still have problems, email me @ csconners@berkeley.edu.

children.subject: It's not 70%-rule specific. It'll also apply to any class where the number of seats in lecture is less than the total number of seats in all sections.

Its not the discussion section being open (the green light on CalCentral). You have to manually ensure that the waitlist for the class is not full. Due to the 70% rule, it is possible for a section to be shown as open yet the waitlist is completely full..
